Now, as part of your class, use `self.column_names` to retain a reference to the original column names from the DataFrame, and you use `data_array` for the actual data operations which is the NumPy array converted from the original DataFrame. When you want to apply feature importance, reference the saved `self.column_names` to locate the column index for weighting.

Be sure to replace the `important_features` and `importance_factor` with actual values you want to use, or modify the constructor to accept these as parameters. The code above will raise an error if an important feature is specified that does not exist in the provided DataFrame.

In summary, this approach allows you to have the original column names and index information for DataFrame-based inputs and lets you perform your weighting logic on the data array directly.
